===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# {{lb|en|semantics}} A word which has the [[opposite]] meaning of another word.
#: {{syn|en|opposite}}
#: {{ant|en|synonym}}
#: {{ux|en|“rich” is an '''antonym''' of “poor”; “full” is an '''antonym''' of “empty”}}
## A word that describes one end of a scale, while its opposite describes the other end, such as ''large'' versus ''small''; a {{l|en|gradable antonym}}.
##* {{quote-book|lang=en|2005|Andrew John Merrison, Aileen Bloomer, Patrick Griffiths and Christopher J. Hall|Introducing Language in Use|http://www.worldcat.org/title/introducing-language-in-use-a-coursebook/oclc/705997377|111|All four lines of the pattern are required to establish that ''hot'' and ''cold'' are '''antonyms'''. <br/>''The water is hot'' entails ''The water is not cold''. <br/>''The water is cold'' entails ''The water is not hot''.<br/>''The water is not hot'' does not entail ''The water is cold''. <br/>''The water is not cold'' does not entail ''The water is hot''.}}

